<subSubSection id="E94DA90DE1985ACA373597C6370C3585" pageId="0" pageNumber="423" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="60845C9DA14E4BE119A03A868004D9D4" pageId="0" pageNumber="423">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5E78E952A516916ABCB5A3CF3EC5D8CB" pageId="0" pageNumber="423">
Body length 4.5-6 mm. Spots on pronotum in shape of narrow stripes (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="CF68FF951FD645A8EA317DDA5F2FC378" captionStart="Figure 1–2" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1 - 2. 1 Dorsal habitus of male Berosus (s. str.) geminus from Yaroslavl Oblast, Russia. 2 Aedagus. A - lateral view, B - side view." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/472150" pageId="0" pageNumber="423">1</figureCitation>
). First abdominal ventrite with small longitudinal keel on the base. Elytral apex rounded, without spine. Interval 4 of elytra with regular row of punctures, bigger punctures visible on elytra interval 3 only. At the sides of elytra - a clear and isolated spot (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="FD6866BE3B726F6F0A124CD41268695C" captionStart="Figure 1–2" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1 - 2. 1 Dorsal habitus of male Berosus (s. str.) geminus from Yaroslavl Oblast, Russia. 2 Aedagus. A - lateral view, B - side view." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/472150" pageId="0" pageNumber="423">1</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus as in Fig. 
<figureCitation id="15BAC2DB4CC14D80B0FCBA4A58DAF7B1" captionStart="Figure 1–2" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1 - 2. 1 Dorsal habitus of male Berosus (s. str.) geminus from Yaroslavl Oblast, Russia. 2 Aedagus. A - lateral view, B - side view." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/472150" pageId="0" pageNumber="423">2</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
<caption id="565526C7038108EBE99E32E24C71BE89" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/472150" pageId="0" pageNumber="423" start="Figure 1–2" startId="F1">
